      Actually I was asking something like this since the first time I saw a Lumia. I liked the hardware but not the software and I miss OpenMoko option of change easily the O.S, back then I wondered about dual booting in a cellphone. <br /><br />I think that with proper storage it can be good, one O.S is gonna be #1 choice but maybe for specific taskes you'll use the other and get the best of both worlds according to your needs (as you do in pc), I'm not a very &quot;social networking&quot;, only chat does it for me so I don't mind rebooting to use any app I need or just exploring novelties of another O.S without having two devices
      
